(304, 176, 'take_action', 'The Web was made to be a global engine of innovation and  entrepreneurship — a level playing field from which we could learn,  connect and create. The FCC''s most recent rule proposal, which would  allow large companies or others to buy faster and more direct Internet  access, threatens that level playing field and the open Web as we know  it. Mozilla has outlined a clear solution giving the FCC authority to protect Net Neutrality, and Congress should make sure the FCC enacts rules that protect all users of the Internet from discrimination. <a href="https://sendto.mozilla.org/page/s/protect-net-neutrality" class="button">Protect Net Neutrality</a>'),
(305, 176, '_take_action', 'field_53ced80eb1274'),
