(6, 1, '2014-07-07 12:00:54', '2014-07-07 19:00:54', '<h3>Building the talent pool to protect the free and open web.</h3>\r\nMozilla Open Web Fellows work with some of the world’s <a title="Host Organizations" href="/host-organizations/">leading nonprofit organizations</a> to help ensure the public policy climate safeguards the Internet as a shared, global and public resource. During the 10-month paid fellowship, we will immerse the next generation of leaders in projects that address key needs with respect to digital freedom: better technical understanding among nonprofit organizations and policy makers of issues; a stronger affirmative agenda that creates better public awareness of internet policy issues; improved cross-sector coordination. Announcing the 2015 Mozilla Open Web Fellows Application -- We are looking for emerging leaders who have a passion for activism in Web issues, a track record of making and contributing to projects -- through technology, organizing, education, etc. -- and an interest in working with Mozilla and host nonprofit organizations on specific initiatives to advance and protect the open Web. Mozilla Open Web Fellows will:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-thumbs-up"></i>Contribute to existing and new projects that create a healthier, more trustworthy Web. This can be accomplished in multiple ways, including technology development, community organizing, education program development, and more.</li>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-comments"></i>Serve as technology advisors, mentors and ambassadors to the partner nonprofit organizations, helping to better inform the Web policy discussion.</li>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-users"></i>Work as a cohort, spending part time embedded within host organizations and part time in the Mozilla San Francisco office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a class="button" href="/application">Apply to be a Fellow</a>\r\n\r\nApplication deadline September 12\r\n<h4>We are thrilled to be partnering with the following Host Organizations</h4>\r\n<div id="org-grid">\r\n<a href="http://publicknowledge.org"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-150" src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/Public-Knowledge.png" alt="Public-Knowledge" width="250" height="39" /></a> <a href="http://amnesty.org"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-121" src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/amnesty.jpg" alt="amnesty" width="250" height="106" /></a> <a href="http://freepress.net"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/freepress.png" alt="freepress" width="250" height="109" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-200" /></a>\r\n<a href="http://oti.newamerica.net"><img class="alignleft size-full" src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/oti.png" alt="oti" width="250" height="75" /></a> <a href="https://www.aclu.org/"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-125" src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/acluf.jpg" alt="acluf" width="250" height="94" /></a>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<small>Photo: Elvert Barnes via Flickr</small>', 'Open Web Fellows', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'open-web-fellows', '', '', '2014-07-29 11:32:37', '2014-07-29 18:32:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost/mozilla/?page_id=6', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(7, 1, '2014-07-07 12:00:54', '2014-07-07 19:00:54', '', 'Open Web Fellows', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-07 12:00:54', '2014-07-07 19:00:54', '', 6, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/07/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(8, 1, '2014-07-07 12:01:22', '2014-07-07 19:01:22', 'The Mozilla fellowships present a unique opportunity for people who want to influence Internet policy. Fellows receive a slate of stipends and benefits to ensure the experience will be a transformative one.\r\n<h5>Financial Benefits</h5>\r\nThe Mozilla Open Web Fellowship is designed to allow flexibility for both Fellows and Partner organizations. The standard Fellowship offers a stipend of $60,000, paid in 10 monthly installments. Fellows are responsible for remitting all applicable taxes and other government payments as required.\r\n\r\nMozilla may, in consultation with Fellows and Partner organizations, elect to vary the amount and duration to accommodate the needs and availability of individual fellows and organizations.\r\n\r\nTo help offset cost of living in the Partner Organization location cities, the Fellowship also provides supplements for housing, childcare, health insurance, moving expenses, and helps pay for research/equipment and books. The Fellowship also covers the costs of required travel for Fellowship activities.\r\n\r\nSupplements below listed as yearly maximums.\r\n\r\n<h5>Housing Supplement (for relocating Fellows only)</h5>\r\n\r\n[table]\r\n[tr][td]Single, married or partnered Fellow[/td] [td]$5,000[/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]Fellow with 1 child[/td] [td]$7,000[/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]Fellow with 2 children[/td] [td]$8,500[/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]Fellow with 3 or more children[/td] [td]$10,000[/td][/tr]\r\n[/table]\r\n\r\n<h5>Child Care Supplement</h5>\r\n\r\n[table]\r\n[tr][td]1 child age 12* or younger[/td] [td]$5,600[/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]2 children ages 12* or younger[/td] [td]$6,000[/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]3 children ages 12* or younger[/td] [td]$6,400[/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]4 or more children ages 12* or younger[/td] [td]$7,200[/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]Additional allowance for child 3* years or younger[/td] [td]$6,400[/td][/tr]\r\n[/table]\r\n\r\n* Age defined on January 1 of Fellowship year.\r\n\r\n<h5>Health Insurance Supplement</h5>\r\nThe Fellowship pays a health insurance supplement for Fellows and their families, ranging from $3,500 for single Fellows to $7,000 for a couple with two or more children. Funds are provided by way of monthly reimbursement.\r\n<h5>Moving Allowance</h5>\r\nUp to $2,000 for Fellows moving between cities within their country of origin. Up to $4,000 for Fellows moving outside their country of origin. The Fellowship also offers a supplemental allowance for families with children of up to $2,000.\r\n<h5>Research/Equipment</h5>\r\nUp to $3,000 annually will be given towards the purchase of laptop computers, digital cameras, recorders, fees for Continuing Studies or other courses related to the Fellowship, computer software, research fees or payments, and travel expenses for conferences or other research related to the Fellow’s research or study.\r\n<h5>Server Allowance</h5>\r\nUp to $250 to cover the server costs associated with deploying projects such as fees for Heroku, Amazon Web Services, and domain registration.\r\n<h5>Travel Allowance</h5>\r\nAll approved Fellowship trips – domestic and international – are covered. Additional travel required by the Partner Organizations will be covered by them.\r\n<h5>Visa Assistance</h5>\r\nMozilla will work directly with Partner Organizations to secure temporary work visas on behalf of Fellows who require them.', 'Benefits', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'benefits', '', '', '2014-07-08 11:24:49', '2014-07-08 18:24:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/mozilla/?page_id=8', 2, 'page', '', 0),
