4">Why do you want to become a Mozilla Open Web Fellow? <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<textarea id="entry_729835304" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.729835304" required="" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n<div id="359634058_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n<div class="required-message">What issue areas are you most passionate about? Why? <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><textarea id="entry_2074095294" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.2074095294" required="" rows="8"></textarea></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-checkbox" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_1423733902">What skills will you bring to the program? <span class="ss-q-help ss-secondary-text" dir="ltr">Select all that apply</span></label><ul class="ss-choices"><li class="ss-choice-item"><label><span class="ss-choice-item-control goog-inline-block"><input id="group_1549395560_1" class="ss-q-checkbox" name="entry.1549395560" type="checkbox" value="web/software development/engineering" /></span><span class="ss-choice-label">web/software development/engineering</span>\r\n</label></li>\r\n	<li class="ss-choice-item"><label><span class="ss-choice-item-control goog-inline-block"><input id="group_1549395560_2" class="ss-q-checkbox" name="entry.1549395560" type="checkbox" value="design" /></span><span class="ss-choice-label">design</span>\r\n</label></li>\r\n	<li class="ss-choice-item"><label><span class="ss-choice-item-control goog-inline-block"><input id="group_1549395560_3" class="ss-q-checkbox" name="entry.1549395560" type="checkbox" value="community organizing" /></span><span class="ss-choice-label">community organizing</span>\r\n</label></li>\r\n	<li class="ss-choice-item"><label><span class="ss-choice-item-control goog-inline-block"><input id="group_1549395560_4" class="ss-q-checkbox" name="entry.1549395560" type="checkbox" value="communications and advocacy" /></span><span class="ss-choice-label">communications and advocacy</span>\r\n</label></li>\r\n	<li class="ss-choice-item"><label><span class="ss-choice-item-control goog-inline-block"><input id="group_1549395560_5" class="ss-q-checkbox" name="entry.1549395560" type="checkbox" value="internet policy" /></span><span class="ss-choice-label">internet policy</span></label></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry">\r\n<div class="ss-q-title">What additional skills and experiences do you have that would contribute to the policy and advocacy arena? <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></div>\r\n<textarea id="entry_370788295" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.370788295" required="" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_1074240666">What tool or campaign idea do you think needs to exist to help inform the policy conversation and why? <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<textarea id="entry_1074240666" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.1074240666" required="" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n<div id="1994553102_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n<div class="required-message">What do you think is an example of an effective advocacy campaign for internet issues over the last year? Why was it effective? <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><textarea id="entry_1213728590" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.1213728590" required="" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n<div id="69577612_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n<div class="required-message">If you are a developer, what are your go-to technologies when building things on the Web?</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><textarea id="entry_1095056798" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.1095056798" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n<div id="368207289_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-section-header" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry">\r\n<h2 class="ss-section-title">Additional Information</h2>\r\n<div class="ss-section-description ss-no-ignore-whitespace"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_1323841396">Do you speak any languages other than English? If yes, please list them.</label>\r\n<input id="entry_1323841396" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.1323841396" type="text" value="" />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_584429587">How did you hear about the Fellowship?</label>\r\n<input id="entry_584429587" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.584429587" type="text" value="" />\r\n<div id="832527952_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<input name="draftResponse" type="hidden" value="[,,&quot;-2670566760985922600&quot;]" />\r\n<input name="pageHistory" type="hidden" value="0" />\r\n<input name="fbzx" type="hidden" value="-2670566760985922600" />\r\n<input id="ss-submit" name="submit" type="submit" value="Send my application" /></div>\r\n</form>', 'Application', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-17 16:51:23', '2014-07-17 23:51:23', '', 4, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/17/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(93, 1, '2014-07-18 10:40:30', '2014-07-18 17:40:30', '<a href="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/nsa.jpg"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/nsa-252x141.jpg" alt="nsa" width="252" height="141" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-25" /></a>\r\n\r\n<h3>Building the talent pool to protect the free and open web.</h3>\r\nMozilla Open Web Fellows work with some of the world’s leading nonprofit organizations to help ensure the public policy climate safeguards the Internet as a shared, global and public resource. During the 10-month paid fellowship, we will immerse the next generation of leaders in projects that address key needs with respect to digital freedom: better technical understanding among nonprofit organizations and policy makers of issues; a stronger affirmative agenda that creates better public awareness of internet policy issues; improved cross-sector coordination. Announcing the 2015 Mozilla Open Web Fellows Application -- We are looking for emerging leaders who have a passion for activism in Web issues, a track record of making and contributing to projects -- through technology, organizing, education, etc. -- and an interest in working with Mozilla and host nonprofit organizations on specific initiatives to advance and protect the open Web. Mozilla Open Web Fellows will:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Contribute to existing and new projects that create a healthier, more trustworthy Web. This can be accomplished in multiple ways, including technology development, community organizing, education program development, and more.</li>\r\n	<li>Serve as technology advisors, mentors and ambassadors to the partner nonprofit organizations, helping to better inform the Web policy discussion.</li>\r\n	<li>Work as a cohort, spending part time embedded within host organizations and part time in the Mozilla San Francisco office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="/policy-contributors/" title="Policy Contributors">Meet our Host Nonprofits</a>.', 'Open Web Fellows', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-18 10:40:30', '2014-07-18 17:40:30', '', 6, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/18/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
