(96, 1, '2014-07-18 10:41:42', '2014-07-18 17:41:42', '<img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/nsa.jpg" alt="nsa" width="690" height="388" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-25" />\r\n\r\n<h3>Building the talent pool to protect the free and open web.</h3>\r\n\r\nMozilla Open Web Fellows work with some of the world’s leading nonprofit organizations to help ensure the public policy climate safeguards the Internet as a shared, global and public resource. During the 10-month paid fellowship, we will immerse the next generation of leaders in projects that address key needs with respect to digital freedom: better technical understanding among nonprofit organizations and policy makers of issues; a stronger affirmative agenda that creates better public awareness of internet policy issues; improved cross-sector coordination. Announcing the 2015 Mozilla Open Web Fellows Application -- We are looking for emerging leaders who have a passion for activism in Web issues, a track record of making and contributing to projects -- through technology, organizing, education, etc. -- and an interest in working with Mozilla and host nonprofit organizations on specific initiatives to advance and protect the open Web. Mozilla Open Web Fellows will:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Contribute to existing and new projects that create a healthier, more trustworthy Web. This can be accomplished in multiple ways, including technology development, community organizing, education program development, and more.</li>\r\n	<li>Serve as technology advisors, mentors and ambassadors to the partner nonprofit organizations, helping to better inform the Web policy discussion.</li>\r\n	<li>Work as a cohort, spending part time embedded within host organizations and part time in the Mozilla San Francisco office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="/policy-contributors/" title="Policy Contributors">Meet our Host Nonprofits</a>.', 'Open Web Fellows', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6-revision-v1', ''