(99, 1, '2014-07-21 09:58:40', '2014-07-21 16:58:40', 'We are thrilled to be working with the following organizations who will serve as hosts for the 2015 Open Web Fellows. These organizations represent the opportunity to advance and protect the free and open Web by building the talent pool of emerging leaders.\r\n\r\n1. Public Knowledge - Public Knowledge preserves the openness of the Internet and the public’s access to knowledge; promotes creativity through balanced copyright; and upholds and protects the rights of consumers to use innovative technology lawfully.\r\n\r\n2. Amnesty International — Amnesty International is a global movement of more than 3 million supporters, members and activists in over 150 countries and territories who campaign to end grave abuses of human rights.\r\n\r\n3. Free Press - Fighting for your rights to connect and communicate, Free Press, and its growing base of 750,000 activists, fights to save the free and open Internet, curb runaway media consolidation, protect press freedom, and ensure diverse voices are represented in our media.\r\n\r\n4. Open Technology Institute — A program of the New America Foundation, The Open Technology Institute formulates policy and regulatory reforms to support open architectures and open source innovations and facilitates the development and implementation of open technologies and communications networks.\r\n\r\n5. American Civil Liberties Union — Founded in 1920, the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) is our nation''s guardian of liberty, working daily in courts, legislatures and communities to defend and preserve the individual rights and liberties that the Constitution and laws of the United States guarantee everyone in this country.', 'Policy Contributors', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-21 09:58:40', '2014-07-21 16:58:40', '', 12, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/21/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(100, 1, '2014-07-22 12:28:41', '2014-07-22 19:28:41', '<img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/nsa.jpg" alt="nsa" width="690" height="388" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-25" />\r\n\r\n<h3>Building the talent pool to protect the free and open web.</h3>\r\n\r\nMozilla Open Web Fellows work with some of the world’s leading nonprofit organizations to help ensure the public policy climate safeguards the Internet as a shared, global and public resource. During the 10-month paid fellowship, we will immerse the next generation of leaders in projects that address key needs with respect to digital freedom: better technical understanding among nonprofit organizations and policy makers of issues; a stronger affirmative agenda that creates better public awareness of internet policy issues; improved cross-sector coordination. Announcing the 2015 Mozilla Open Web Fellows Application -- We are looking for emerging leaders who have a passion for activism in Web issues, a track record of making and contributing to projects -- through technology, organizing, education, etc. -- and an interest in working with Mozilla and host nonprofit organizations on specific initiatives to advance and protect the open Web. Mozilla Open Web Fellows will:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Contribute to existing and new projects that create a healthier, more trustworthy Web. This can be accomplished in multiple ways, including technology development, community organizing, education program development, and more.</li>\r\n	<li>Serve as technology advisors, mentors and ambassadors to the partner nonprofit organizations, helping to better inform the Web policy discussion.</li>\r\n	<li>Work as a cohort, spending part time embedded within host organizations and part time in the Mozilla San Francisco office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="/policy-contributors/" title="Policy Contributors">Meet our Host Nonprofits</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href="/application" class="button">Apply to be a Fellow</a>\r\nApplication deadline September 12', 'Open Web Fellows', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-22 12:28:41', '2014-07-22 19:28:41', '', 6, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/22/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(101, 1, '2014-07-22 12:30:05', '2014-07-22 19:30:05', '[accordion multiopen="true"]\r\n[toggle title="When is the application deadline?" state="opened"]\r\n\r\nOur application deadline is 11:59pm PT on Friday, September 12, 2014. We will be announcing our new Fellows at the 2014 Mozilla Festival in London, October 24-26.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n[toggle title="What is a “fellow” anyway?"]\r\n\r\nWhen we say “fellow” we don’t mean “man.” A fellow is someone who “shares a particular activity, quality, or condition with someone.” Fellowship programs bring together a diverse collection of people with shared skills and experiences to spend time and collaborate together.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="I am not an engineer. Should I still apply?"]\r\n\r\nAbsolutely! There is no requirement for a particular programming language or development skillset. A lot of policy change happens through community organizing, campaign design and other non-engineering skill sets.\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="What type of applicants are you looking for?"]\r\n\r\nIf you have a knack for coding and an interest in contributing your skills to internet policy projects, you are the type of person we are looking for. There is no “typical” Fellow.\r\n\r\nWe are an inclusive program and seek Fellows that reflect the diversity of the communities we serve. Women and other under-represented participants in technology are strongly encouraged to apply for a Mozilla Open Web Fellowship.\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="I don’t speak English very well or live in the U.S. Can I still participate?"]\r\n\r\nWe are an international program and welcome participants from around the world. You do not need to be a U.S. citizen to participate in the program. We assist Fellows with any necessary visa applications for working and traveling during the Fellowship. Perfect English is not a requirement, however please be aware that it may be challenging to participate in some aspects of our program if your English is limited.\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="Where will the fellows be based? How are the fellows matched with news organizations?"]\r\n\r\nFellows will split time between their host organization and the Mozilla San Francisco office\r\n\r\nIn 2015, the Fellows will be based with:\r\nINSERT ORGS\r\n\r\nWe make every attempt to match skills of Fellows with needs of partner organizations when matching Fellow to organization.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="What are you looking for with the example projects on the application?"]\r\n\r\nWe want to see three projects that you are proud of. Tell us why you’re excited about the project, and if you made the project has part of a team, describe the contribution that you made. The examples you include are not shared beyond the small pool of application reviewers.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="What if my example projects don’t include open source or technology contributions?"]\r\n\r\nThat’s ok. We understand that a lot of people have done work that is not open source and that a lot of policy and advocacy work is not technology specific. You will be building in the open and contributing back to open source projects as a Fellow, but it is not a requirement to have done this before applying.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="What is the timeline after the Fellowship deadline closes?"]\r\n\r\nThe Fellowship application opened on {INSERT DATE} and closes September 12, 2014. After September 12, all applications will be reviewed by a small reviewing panel. By early October, a final batch of 20-30 semifinalists will be selected and interviews conducted. Finalists will be notified by mid October and a public announcement of our 2015 fellows will be made at the Mozilla Festival in London October 24, 2014.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="What kind of competition are you expecting with the Fellowship?"]\r\n\r\nThis is the first year of the Open Web Fellows search process, so it’s difficult to gauge the level of competition. For comparison, the Mozilla-Knight OpenNews Fellowship program receives hundreds of qualified applications for a limited amount of Fellowship openings.\r\nIn terms of the applicant pool, we are committed to matching the skills of the Fellow to the needs of the news organization. It’s a very individualized matching process.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="How does the application review and matching process work?"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Applications are <a href="/application/">submitted online</a> and are visible at the time they are submitted, but formal review does not begin until after the application deadline closes on September 12.</li>\r\n	<li>Mozilla''s policy and advocacy staff review all of the applications and cull the batch to a manageable number for the partner organizations to review.</li>\r\n	<li>The partners review this shorter list and submit a list of the five people they are most interested in learning more about.</li>\r\n	<li>These semifinalists are contacted for interviews. Applicants who are not moving forward in the selection process are notified.</li>\r\n	<li>Mozilla’s policy and advocacy team conduct short, standardized interviews with the semifinalists, asking a few questions that are about vision and skills/practical considerations.</li>\r\n	<li>The notes from these interviews are submitted back to the partner organizations for review, and the partners are able to pick their top three finalists from the entire pool of semifinalists, not just the five they initially submitted.</li>\r\n	<li>The semifinalists that are not moving forward are notified of their application status.</li>\r\n	<li>The partner organization and Mozilla’s policy and advocacy team has a much longer interview with each of the partner organization’s top three candidates. This interview is a chance for the partner organization and the finalist to learn more about each other and what to expect from a Fellowship at that host organization.</li>\r\n	<li>In consultation with Mozilla’s policy and advocacy team and the partner organizations, the final Fellow selection is made for each organization.</li>\r\n	<li>The selected Fellows are notified and given an opportunity to ask additional questions of the partner organization and Mozilla.</li>\r\n	<li>The finalists that were not selected as Fellows are notified of their application status.</li>\r\n	<li>A public announcement of the Fellows is made at the Mozilla Festival.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="What is the timeline for the Fellowship?"]\r\n\r\n2015 Fellowships begin in January 2015 and last for 10 months. Each Fellows'' start date will be individualized for the needs of that Fellow and the partner organization.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="What type of projects do the fellows work on?"]\r\n\r\nThat is dictated by the partner organization and the Fellow. We expect that these projects will reflect a range of policy and advocacy activities, including program/campaign development, technology issue analysis, data crunching, etc. We’re looking for talented people who want to collaborate with partner organizations to advance existing projects and to create new ones. In collaboration with Mozilla, the other Fellows, and the partner organizations, Fellows get a lot of room to figure out what the projects will be.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="Are you still accepting applications for host organizations?"]\r\n\r\nNo, we are not accepting host newsroom applications at this time.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="Why is Mozilla interested in policy and advocacy?"]\r\n\r\nAnswer here\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="Who is sponsoring the Open Web Fellows Program?"]\r\n\r\nFord, Google, etc.\r\n\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[toggle title="How do I contact you?"]\r\n\r\nWe’re very reachable. You can e-mail us, find us on Twitter or Facebook, reach us at our monthly community calls, and even catch us on IRC via the #openweb channel on irc.mozilla.org. We’d love to hear from you and are happy to answer any questions you may have. [ add links ]\r\n[/toggle]\r\n\r\n[/accordion]', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '10-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-22 12:30:05', '2014-07-22 19:30:05', '', 10, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/22/10-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(102, 1, '2014-07-22 12:30:51', '2014-07-22 19:30:51', 'Are you a developer, technologist, designer, community organizer, policy nut that wants to help save the Internet, and keep it free and open? <strong>Apply to become a 2015 Mozilla Open Web Fellow.</strong>\r\n\r\nSpend ten months embedded in one of the world’s leading nonprofit and advocacy organizations developing tools and campaigns, helping inform and influence the global Internet policy discussion, and becoming a leader in the international policy community. <a href="http://policy.mozilla.org/faq/">Learn&nbsp;more</a>\r\n\r\n<span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span> Required\r\n\r\n<form id="ss-form" action="https://docs.google.com/a/erikarathje.ca/forms/d/1qHke2PWGy-vrQ8wb9V2uWVmgh8g0GGJ0PQ1JMOhkvVs/formResponse" method="POST" target="_self">\r\n<div class="errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-section-header" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry">\r\n<h2 class="ss-section-title">About You</h2>\r\n<div class="ss-section-description ss-no-ignore-whitespace"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_1383633285">\r\nFirst Name <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<input id="entry_1383633285" class="ss-q-short" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.1383633285" required="" type="text" value="" />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_359386430">Last Name <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<input id="entry_359386430" class="ss-q-short" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.359386430" required="" type="text" value="" />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_710867802">Email address <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<input id="entry_710867802" class="ss-q-short" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.710867802" required="" type="email" value="" />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_1553377728">Country <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<input id="entry_1553377728" class="ss-q-short" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.1553377728" required="" type="text" value="" />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_755037102">City <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<input id="entry_755037102" class="ss-q-short" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.755037102" required="" type="text" value="" />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_1647764247">Phone Number</label>\r\n<input id="entry_1647764247" class="ss-q-short" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.1647764247" type="text" value="" />\r\n<div id="207632299_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_564738507">Twitter handle</label>\r\n<input id="entry_564738507" class="ss-q-short" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.564738507" type="text" value="" />\r\n<div id="1103777452_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-section-header" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry">\r\n<h2 class="ss-section-title">About Your Work</h2>\r\n<div class="ss-section-description ss-no-ignore-whitespace"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_570885793">Website or portfolio (link)</label>\r\n<input id="entry_570885793" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.570885793" type="text" value="" />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_897793086">Resume or LinkedIn profile (link)</label>\r\n<input id="entry_897793086" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.897793086" type="text" value="" />\r\n<div id="1083312311_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry">\r\n<div class="ss-q-title">Please describe a project you''ve worked on that you were particularly proud of and why. <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></div>\r\n<textarea id="entry_29741206" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.29741206" required="" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n<div id="1687309464_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-section-header" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry">\r\n<h2 class="ss-section-title">Tell Us More About You</h2>\r\n<div class="ss-section-description ss-no-ignore-whitespace"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_729835304">Why do you want to become a Mozilla Open Web Fellow? <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<textarea id="entry_729835304" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.729835304" required="" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n<div id="359634058_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n<div class="required-message">What issue areas are you most passionate about? Why? <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><textarea id="entry_2074095294" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.2074095294" required="" rows="8"></textarea></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-checkbox" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_1423733902">What skills will you bring to the program? <span class="ss-q-help ss-secondary-text" dir="ltr">Select all that apply</span></label><ul class="ss-choices"><li class="ss-choice-item"><label><span class="ss-choice-item-control goog-inline-block"><input id="group_1549395560_1" class="ss-q-checkbox" name="entry.1549395560" type="checkbox" value="web/software development/engineering" /></span><span class="ss-choice-label">web/software development/engineering</span>\r\n</label></li>\r\n	<li class="ss-choice-item"><label><span class="ss-choice-item-control goog-inline-block"><input id="group_1549395560_2" class="ss-q-checkbox" name="entry.1549395560" type="checkbox" value="design" /></span><span class="ss-choice-label">design</span>\r\n</label></li>\r\n	<li class="ss-choice-item"><label><span class="ss-choice-item-control goog-inline-block"><input id="group_1549395560_3" class="ss-q-checkbox" name="entry.1549395560" type="checkbox" value="community organizing" /></span><span class="ss-choice-label">community organizing</span>\r\n</label></li>\r\n	<li class="ss-choice-item"><label><span class="ss-choice-item-control goog-inline-block"><input id="group_1549395560_4" class="ss-q-checkbox" name="entry.1549395560" type="checkbox" value="communications and advocacy" /></span><span class="ss-choice-label">communications and advocacy</span>\r\n</label></li>\r\n	<li class="ss-choice-item"><label><span class="ss-choice-item-control goog-inline-block"><input id="group_1549395560_5" class="ss-q-checkbox" name="entry.1549395560" type="checkbox" value="internet policy" /></span><span class="ss-choice-label">internet policy</span></label></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry">\r\n<div class="ss-q-title">What additional skills and experiences do you have that would contribute to the policy and advocacy arena? <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></div>\r\n<textarea id="entry_370788295" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.370788295" required="" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_1074240666">What tool or campaign idea do you think needs to exist to help inform the policy conversation and why? <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<textarea id="entry_1074240666" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.1074240666" required="" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n<div id="1994553102_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n<div class="required-message">What do you think is an example of an effective advocacy campaign for internet issues over the last year? Why was it effective? <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><textarea id="entry_1213728590" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.1213728590" required="" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n<div id="69577612_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n<div class="required-message">If you are a developer, what are your go-to technologies when building things on the Web?</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-paragraph-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><textarea id="entry_1095056798" class="ss-q-long" dir="auto" cols="0" name="entry.1095056798" rows="8"></textarea>\r\n<div id="368207289_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-section-header" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry">\r\n<h2 class="ss-section-title">Additional Information</h2>\r\n<div class="ss-section-description ss-no-ignore-whitespace"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_1323841396">Do you speak any languages other than English? If yes, please list them.</label>\r\n<input id="entry_1323841396" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.1323841396" type="text" value="" />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_584429587">How did you hear about the Fellowship?</label>\r\n<input id="entry_584429587" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.584429587" type="text" value="" />\r\n<div id="832527952_errorMessage" class="error-message"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<input name="draftResponse" type="hidden" value="[,,&quot;-2670566760985922600&quot;]" />\r\n<input name="pageHistory" type="hidden" value="0" />\r\n<input name="fbzx" type="hidden" value="-2670566760985922600" />\r\n<input id="ss-submit" name="submit" type="submit" value="Submit my application" /></div>\r\n</form>', 'Application', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-22 12:30:51', '2014-07-22 19:30:51', '', 4, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/22/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(103, 1, '2014-07-22 12:31:42', '2014-07-22 19:31:42', '<h3>We are Building a Global Movement to Protect the Free and Open Web</h3>\r\nMozilla’s Open Web Policy program is aimed at advancing and protecting the free and open web. We’re helping the global network of developers, makers and organizers create tools and programs to enable organizations to help shape policy, and policy makers to understand the impact of their policy on the Internet.', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '21-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-22 12:31:42', '2014-07-22 19:31:42', '', 21, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/22/21-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
