(132, 1, '2014-07-23 17:05:21', '2014-07-24 00:05:21', 'We are thrilled to be working with the following organizations who will serve as hosts for the 2015 Open Web Fellows. These organizations represent the opportunity to advance and protect the free and open Web by building the talent pool of emerging leaders.\r\n\r\n<div id="orgs">\r\n<span><strong>Public Knowledge</strong> — Public Knowledge preserves the openness of the Internet and the public’s access to knowledge; promotes creativity through balanced copyright; and upholds and protects the rights of consumers to use innovative technology lawfully.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.amnesty.org"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/amnesty.jpg" alt="amnesty" width="250" height="106" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-121" /></a> <span><strong>Amnesty International</strong> — Amnesty International is a global movement of more than 3 million supporters, members and activists in over 150 countries and territories who campaign to end grave abuses of human rights.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.freepress.net"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/freepress.jpg" alt="freepress" width="250" height="100" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-123" /></a> <span><strong>Free Press</strong> — Fighting for your rights to connect and communicate, Free Press, and its growing base of 750,000 activists, fights to save the free and open Internet, curb runaway media consolidation, protect press freedom, and ensure diverse voices are represented in our media.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://oti.newamerica.net"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/oti.jpg" alt="oti" width="250" height="75" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-124" /></a> <span><strong>Open Technology Institute</strong> — A program of the New America Foundation, The Open Technology Institute formulates policy and regulatory reforms to support open architectures and open source innovations and facilitates the development and implementation of open technologies and communications networks.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://www.aclu.org"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/acluf.jpg" alt="acluf" width="250" height="94" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-125" /></a> <span><strong>American Civil Liberties Union</strong> — Founded in 1920, the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) is our nation''s guardian of liberty, working daily in courts, legislatures and communities to defend and preserve the individual rights and liberties that the Constitution and laws of the United States guarantee everyone in this country.</span>\r\n</div>', 'Policy Contributors', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-23 17:05:21', '2014-07-24 00:05:21', '', 12, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/23/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(133, 1, '2014-07-24 09:43:49', '2014-07-24 16:43:49', 'Are you a developer, technologist, designer, community organizer, or policy nut that wants to help save the Internet, and keep it free and open? <strong>Apply to become a 2015 Mozilla Open Web Fellow.</strong>\r\n\r\nSpend ten months embedded in one of the world’s leading nonprofit and advocacy organizations developing tools and campaigns, helping inform and influence the global Internet policy discussion, and becoming a leader in the international policy community. <a href="http://policy.mozilla.org/faq/">Learn&nbsp;more</a>\r\n\r\n<span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span> Required\r\n\r\n<form id="ss-form" action="https://docs.google.com/a/erikarathje.ca/forms/d/1qHke2PWGy-vrQ8wb9V2uWVmgh8g0GGJ0PQ1JMOhkvVs/formResponse" method="POST" target="_self">\r\n<div id="twocol">\r\n<div class="errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item  ss-section-header" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry">\r\n<h2 class="ss-section-title">About You</h2>\r\n<div class="ss-section-description ss-no-ignore-whitespace"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_1383633285">\r\nFirst Name <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<input id="entry_1383633285" class="ss-q-short" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.1383633285" required="" type="text" value="" />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="ss-item ss-item-required ss-text" dir="ltr">\r\n<div class="ss-form-entry"><label class="ss-q-item-label" for="entry_359386430">Last Name <span class="ss-required-asterisk">*</span></label>\r\n<input id="entry_359386430" class="ss-q-short" dir="auto" title="" name="entry.359386430" required="" type="text" value="" />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="ss-form-question errorbox-good">\r\n<div class="s