(151, 1, '2014-07-24 11:30:23', '2014-07-24 18:30:23', 'We are thrilled to be working with the following organizations who will serve as hosts for the 2015 Open Web Fellows. These organizations represent the opportunity to advance and protect the free and open Web by building the talent pool of emerging leaders.\r\n\r\n<div id="orgs">\r\n<a href="https://www.publicknowledge.org"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/Public-Knowledge.png" alt="Public-Knowledge" width="250" height="39" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-150" /></a> <span><strong>Public Knowledge</strong> — Public Knowledge preserves the openness of the Internet and the public’s access to knowledge; promotes creativity through balanced copyright; and upholds and protects the rights of consumers to use innovative technology lawfully.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.amnesty.org"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/amnesty.jpg" alt="amnesty" width="250" height="106" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-121" /></a> <span><strong>Amnesty International</strong> — Amnesty International is a global movement of more than 3 million supporters, members and activists in over 150 countries and territories who campaign to end grave abuses of human rights.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.freepress.net"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/freepress.jpg" alt="freepress" width="250" height="100" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-123" /></a> <span><strong>Free Press</strong> — Fighting for your rights to connect and communicate, Free Press, and its growing base of 750,000 activists, fights to save the free and open Internet, curb runaway media consolidation, protect press freedom, and ensure diverse voices are represented in our media.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://oti.newamerica.net"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/oti.jpg" alt="oti" width="250" height="75" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-124" /></a> <span><strong>Open Technology Institute</strong> — A program of the New America Foundation, The Open Technology Institute formulates policy and regulatory reforms to support open architectures and open source innovations and facilitates the development and implementation of open technologies and communications networks.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://www.aclu.org"><img src="http://localhost/mozilla/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2014/07/acluf.jpg" alt="acluf" width="250" height="94" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-125" /></a> <span><strong>American Civil Liberties Union</strong> — Founded in 1920, the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) is our nation''s guardian of liberty, working daily in courts, legislatures and communities to defend and preserve the individual rights and liberties that the Constitution and laws of the United States guarantee everyone in this country.</span>\r\n</div>', 'Policy Contributors', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-24 11:30:23', '2014-07-24 18:30:23', '', 12, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/24/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(155, 1, '2014-07-24 12:04:42', '2014-07-24 19:04:42', '<h3>Building the talent pool to protect the free and open web.</h3>\r\n\r\nMozilla Open Web Fellows work with some of the world’s leading nonprofit organizations to help ensure the public policy climate safeguards the Internet as a shared, global and public resource. During the 10-month paid fellowship, we will immerse the next generation of leaders in projects that address key needs with respect to digital freedom: better technical understanding among nonprofit organizations and policy makers of issues; a stronger affirmative agenda that creates better public awareness of internet policy issues; improved cross-sector coordination. Announcing the 2015 Mozilla Open Web Fellows Application -- We are looking for emerging leaders who have a passion for activism in Web issues, a track record of making and contributing to projects -- through technology, organizing, education, etc. -- and an interest in working with Mozilla and host nonprofit organizations on specific initiatives to advance and protect the open Web. Mozilla Open Web Fellows will:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-thumbs-up"></i>Contribute to existing and new projects that create a healthier, more trustworthy Web. This can be accomplished in multiple ways, including technology development, community organizing, education program development, and more.</li>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-comments"></i>Serve as technology advisors, mentors and ambassadors to the partner nonprofit organizations, helping to better inform the Web policy discussion.</li>\r\n	<li><i class="fa fa-users"></i>Work as a cohort, spending part time embedded within host organizations and part time in the Mozilla San Francisco office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="/policy-contributors/" title="Policy Contributors">Meet our Host Nonprofits</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href="/application" class="button">Apply to be a Fellow</a>\r\n\r\nApplication deadline September 12', 'Open Web Fellows', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-24 12:04:42', '2014-07-24 19:04:42', '', 6, 'http://localhost/mozilla/2014/07/24/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
